Doc Spatz,<br>
     I for one didn't bring it up because I did some things I'm not too proud of, especially with the way I failed to properly break a 2 month relationship, but just didn't go back.  This may sound strange to some, but the worst agony I went through in Vietnam was 2 weeks of soul searching after losing my virginity.  12 years of Notre Dame nuns in the '50s &amp; '60s was not without lasting effect.  I know, I know, there is absolutely no comparison with what a lot of guys went through in combat, but for me at the time it was serious, and I was a royal pain in the neck with my guilt trip to everybody else for a while.  
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.mil  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


